Female.description: Pine Grosbeaks have stubbier bills than Evening Grosbeaks. Females have greenish-yellow on the head, unlike the female Evening Grosbeak’s gray head. Pine Grosbeaks have gray wings with white wingbars, whereas Evening Grosbeaks have black wings with a large white patch.

Breeding male.description: American Goldfinches are much smaller with smaller bills than Evening Grosbeaks. Breeding males also lack the male Evening Grosbeak's large white wing patches.

Nonbreeding male.description: American Goldfinches are much smaller with smaller bills than Evening Grosbeaks. Nonbreeding males have brown bodies with contrasting black wings, unlike the grayish bodies of female Evening Grosbeaks.
